      "review_summary": "The PR changes Memory Wiki ingest to derive source page IDs and paths from a readable slug plus canonical source-path hash, reuse legacy source pages by source path, and add focused ingest regression tests.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: current main computes `pageId` and `pageRelativePath` solely from `slugifyWikiSegment(title)`, so two different files with titles like `hello world` and `hello-world` write the same source page. I did not execute the CLI because this review is read-only.",
