      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-wiki): prevent ingested source page collisions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #65965.\n\nThis PR prevents ingested memory-wiki source pages from silently overwriting each other when different source files normalize to the same readable slug.\n\nPreviously, `ingestMemoryWikiSource(...)` derived both `pageId` and `pageRelativePath` directly from the slugified title. Different files could therefore collapse onto the same `source.<slug>` / `sources/<slug>.md` identity, especially with non-ASCII titles or repeated fallback-heavy names.\n\nThis keeps source page names readable, but adds a stable source-path-derived suffix for new source page identities.\n\n## What changed\n\n- keep the readable slug prefix for ingested source pages\n- add a stable 12-hex hash suffix derived from the canonical source path for new source identities\n- use the same resolved identity consistently for both:\n  - `pageId`\n  - `pageRelativePath`\n- preserve legacy `source.<slug>` identities when re-ingesting existing vaults\n- canonicalize source paths for identity matching, including symlink aliases where possible\n- derive fallback titles from the user-provided path so symlinked inputs keep the expected user-facing name\n- limit the compatibility lookup to source pages rather than scanning every queryable wiki page\n\n## Regression coverage\n\nAdded focused coverage for:\n\n- pure CJK titles no longer collapsing to the same source page\n- similar titles with the same slug no longer overwriting each other\n- repeated ingest of the same source remaining stable\n- plain ASCII titles remaining readable and stable\n- identical titles with different source paths remaining distinct\n- existing legacy source pages being reused on re-ingest\n- symlinked source paths resolving to the same source identity\n- fallback titles using the user-provided input path rather than the canonical target filename\n- compatibility lookup scanning only source pages\n\n## Testing\n\nPassed locally:\n\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/memory-wiki/src/ingest.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/memory-wiki`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/memory-wiki/src/ingest.ts extensions/memory-wiki/src/ingest.test.ts`\n\nGitHub Actions are green on the latest head commit.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis PR intentionally stays focused on preventing source page identity collisions.\n\nIt does not redesign the broader wiki identity system, and it does not attempt to migrate or repair historical collisions already present in existing vaults.\n\nOne remaining performance trade-off is that ingest still performs a source-page compatibility lookup before compiling the vault. This is now limited to `sources/*.md`, not all queryable wiki pages. Removing that scan entirely would likely require a broader source identity index or compile-metadata reuse path, so I am leaving that as a follow-up unless maintainers prefer it included before merge.\n\n## Version context\n\nThe issue was reported against OpenClaw 2026.4.11, but this fix is developed against current `main`.",
        "branch": "codex/memory-wiki-source-collision",
